Not set today, which means same-origin only — safe by default. But teams often reach for `app.use(cors())` which is effectively `*`. Pre-empt that:
```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({ origin: ['https://app.example.com'], credentials: true }));
```
Never combine `origin: '*'` with `credentials: true` (browsers block it, but people try).

